Product Description

Tynor Knee Support Hinged (Neoprene) provides compression & side support through rigid hinges. It retains body heat for pain relief & faster healing, allows natural knee movement & offers a snug fit. Ideal for injuries & post-surgical recovery.

Previous page

  1. Durable 3-Layer Neoprene

    Neoprene layer bonded with nylon fabric on both sides provides 4-way stretch for warmth & durability

  2. Patellar Support

    Silicon padding and patellar opening support patella alignment and comfort.

  3. Adjustable & Easy to Use

    Hook-loop closures ensure snug fit, easy wear, and customized compression control.

  4. Bi axial aluminum hinge

    Mimics the natural knee joint, allowing free flexion movement while ensuring full weight bearing.

  5. Therapeutic Warmth

    Retains body heat for faster healing and lasting pain relief during activity or rest.

      4.0 out of 5 stars Practical product but ... READ BEFORE YOU BUY ....
      Reviewed in India on 16 June 2017
      Size: LVerified Purchase
      Brand : Tynor
      Product : Neoprene Hinged Knee Support
      Size : Large
      MRP : INR 1069

      We needed to get a supportive brace for our mom (52) as she has issues with her knee. We bought a large size which is a rather comfortable fit even on a bulky person. Here are some points that I observed :

      --- THE GOOD ---

      1. EASY APPLICATION: Simple wrap around design allows easy application and adjustment. It has a simple velcro strapping systemand non-slip feature of the material keeps the brace in place even during extended use.

      2. COMFORTABLE AND LIGHTWEIGHT : The offset bicentric hinges are light and help to relieve the pressure at the knee joint. For custom support the patellar ring can change position and ease the movement.

      3. CONTROLS SWELLING: Constructed from a very compressive material, this brace helps to control pain and swelling in the knee joint. See size chart in second image for sizing measurements to ensure a correct and comfortable fit.

      4. BIAXIAL SUPPORT HINGES FOR LATERAL STABILITY: The Biaxial hinges are located on both sides of the knee for added support. It improves medial and lateral stability in turn helping reduce injury and assist recovery.This also helps with strains, sprains, instability and patellar tracking.

      5. INJURY SUPPORT: This material provides compression support to injured joints , muscles , ligaments and tendons.

      --- THE BAD ----

      1. ALLERGENIC: The material is NOT breathable . It can be allergenic for some because it is made up of Neoprene . Skin contact with Neoprene can cause two kind of dermatological risks if it doesnt suit you : (A) Allergic Contact Dermatitis (ACD) or (B) Miliria Rubra ( Prickly heat) . It also has silicon buttress along the patella opening.

      2. NOT VERY DURABLE : Mom has been using this for about a year now . The outer covering has kind of ripped off and the hinges have started to show up from the ripped out fabric.

      3. SWEATING : Since the fabric is not breathable it causes a lot of sweating on the inside .
      I would say it is fine just as long as you can take it on and off. Also try to wear something underneath to avoid the blisters.

      ---BOTTOMLINE---
      Irrespective of the flaws , my mom loves this . Luckily it did not have any side-effects on her skin . In any case, the brace has been working well and taking pressure off the knee .

    Product description
